node.text:
“50 Cent got me to the top. Curtis Jackson keeps me there.” 

Classic Jessie Lee - find a book, tear through it, train from it 🤣❤️

I got Curtis Jackson’s book yesterday. I’m done reading it. Absurdly good book, for the record. 

I’ve tried to explain the alter ego in many ways on my social media before. 

I’ve never heard it said so perfectly.

He wrote about how every successful person he knows has a different side to them. It’s different than who is on the stage, who is in the videos, who performs.

My body has been hurting so much since this Lyme flare and for the first time ever this weekend my company got to see a lot more Jessie Lee than they have before. 

I’m extremely soft. I don’t like being talked badly about. I’m highly emotional. I’m extremely intuitive and energetically aware. I’m obsessed with love. Empathy is my number one core value. I would rather spend time with children than adults. I love a good book and a cup of tea. I revel in silence. 

BOSSLEE got me to the top.
Jessie Lee keeps me there.

If this makes sense to you, drop me a heart ❤️ 
#bosslee #jessielee

node.text:
Today @50cent came to our event and 🤣🤣🤣 I’m sorry I can’t stop thinking about how HE came out and said how HE knows ME. And addressed me by name in front of our entire company. Talked about how he met our company’s top earner Jessie Lee months back. The audience screamed. I was like what the f. 

I made a very distinct decision at the beginning of quarantine that I was going to raise my standards like my shirt says. I said I was going to go all out. I was going to get better. More people would know who I am. I was going to impact way more lives. I took quarantine as a time to get an edge. 

Today was just one of those moments. 

How many of you think he listens to my podcast? 🤣❤️🤣❤️🤣

Curtis Jackson - 50 - said so many incredible quotes today. I’ll give you a few… 

“People become complacent after they achieve some type of success. Create a new bar” 

“The project can only be as good as the passion you put into it”

“If you don’t have competitors then create them.”

“Competitive advantage let’s you hold the title.”

“You’re not going to out work me.”

Backstage before I went on today I read the first 30 pages of his book - and THAT MAN KNOWS WHAT HE’S TALKING ABOUT 👏👏👏👏👏

Do you want to level up? In any way? If you do, drop me a ❤️ because it’s time.

#bosslee

node.text:
Four years ago today I walked into an office building in McKinney, Texas and let a very bent but not yet broken Jessie Lee listen to an idea. 

In a flurry a man in a blue Gucci jacket with a flower on the pocket stormed into the room late but excited to meet me. 

My whole intuition said yes in that moment. It wasn’t until 6 weeks later I actually partnered with him in business, but today’s the day I knew. 

I love you so much, @brianundy. We’re better every day even if it’s 1%. We’ve come incredibly far, touched millions of lives and how excited this is basically day 1.

Thank you for letting me run. Thank you for loving me. Thank you for listening. Thank you for not quitting. Thank you for being the drop that created this massive ripple. 

28 countries is nothing. I’m ready for MORE. 

And I’m so thankful to be doing it with you. 

Because it’s been 4 years, and I’ve proven everything I said then…I’ll keep making promises and keep filling them. I’m so PROUD of what we do. I’m so happy for what we’ve done. I’m so grateful for the opportunity to partner with anyone around the world ready to say yes. 

I’m breaking through. Are you? ❤️

Drop below what country you think we should open next? 

#bosslee

node.text:
I could pretend I’m sleeping but I’m actually basically weeping in my hotel room covered head to toe in sweat after our first day back at an event in 565 days. 

How things can feel such a combination of light and heavy at the same time is sort of indescribable. I don’t even know if that makes sense. 

We had Nadia Nadim speak today at our event and everything out of her mouth seemed like it was meant to hit me between the eyes. As as Afghan refugee the strength the woman has to persevere cuts through a room like a hot knife. 

I lost it when she didn’t even finish a thought. She was trying to explain why it is a goal to be rich. She said “because it’s not fair…” until she burst into tears. 

Have you ever felt like that? 

I FEEL LIKE THAT SO MUCH MORE THAN I WANT TO ADMIT. 

At the beginning of the event today our ceo asked us to write down why we’re here. I know what kind of event this is, lol. It’s all personal development. I wrote down a lot, but in particular a long bit about breaking a pattern I adopted a LONG time ago. 

I’m typing and erasing (anyone else do this?? lol) so I’ll stop 🛑 at this for now, but I will say…

Stepping on a physical stage for the first time in over a year felt REALLY good, and also super barfy haha. I’m here to heal. 

If you’re going through these last 18 months and trying to heal and are down with doing it together…drop me a heart ❤️ 

#bosslee

node.text:
Do MORE. Be MORE. Give MORE. 

My heart is full. 

Impromptu group photo. 

3 hours of extroverting so far and I feel like I’ve been run over by an entire bus 🤣🤣

But my love and gratitude right now 😭 I’m so emotional seeing these people. 

I said everyone get behind me for the photo and then have car earners in front. 

This group of people was just standing around and I’m like what the heck…get behind…

Then I realized we have almost 70 car earners at this event 😭😭😭😭😭😭

It’s super cool to be on top. IT IS ABSOLUTELY BREATHTAKING to take so many with you. 

My heart could burst. Not even 4 years yet…

First event back from the pandemic. Just. All the feels.

Are you here? Don’t forget to say hi! I’m not hugging but I’m totally taking photos. 

#bosslee

node.text:
Why network marketing?

Magic moments. 

Brooke was trying to get me to the airport like an hour and a half early for our flight to Kentucky today and I was disinterested 🤣🤣🤣

I reached out to my friend and business partner and asked if he had room on a jet. Uh. LOL. This jet is a 737 hahahahahahh it flies globally. 

Today, it flew to Kentucky where we landed and I took Brian’s Beeeeaaaauuutiful Bentley for the week. 

Brooke goes “b’s everywhere! For me!!”

When I started mentoring and coaching Brooke she told me she doesn’t get on planes. She said she would never fly. 

Oh my, how your life can change when you’re coachable and don’t give up when it’s hard. 

Now we’re at a Brazilian steakhouse grubbing and hanging out with our best friends 😉 ❤️ 

Do you ever want to fly private? 
#bosslee
